info","should_display_ad_info":false},"serialized_frtp_identifiers":null,"debug_info":null,"inform_treatment_for_community_notes":null,"message":{"text":"As you may know, our beloved resort was recently impacted by Hurricane Helene, which brought significant flooding to the area. Unfortunately, every building, except one, experienced damage, leading us to make the difficult decision to temporarily close for the next 2 months or so. During this time, we are working tirelessly to renovate the affected areas and ensure that when we welcome you back, Plantation On Crystal River will be better than ever before.\n\nWe want to take a moment to apologize to all our guests who had reservations during this period. We understand the inconvenience this may cause, and our team will be reaching out to each of you who haven\u2019t yet had the opportunity to reschedule or cancel your reservations. Your comfort and satisfaction remain our utmost priority.\n\nWe also want to thank our incredible fishing guides for their unwavering dedication in fixing the docks. Thanks to their hard work, the docks are back up and running, and charters are already heading out and catching some quality fish. So, while the rooms aren\u2019t quite ready for reservations, the fish are biting and the water is navigable. We are so grateful for their support, and we encourage you to take advantage of a great day out on the water with our fishing guides.\n\nWe are committed to not only restoring but enhancing every corner of the resort, ensuring that the beauty and experience you\u2019ve come to love will continue to thrive. We are taking every step to turn over every stone, making sure every detail is taken care of for your return.
